dataDictionary.Title: PDS4 Data Dictionary
dataDictionary.Description: This document is a dump of the contents of the PDS4 Data Dictionary

class.title: Augmentation_Method
class.description: The Augmentation_Method class contains information about a data set's augmentation method.

class.title: Calibration_Method
class.description: The Calibration_Method class is a container for classes and and attributes describing the Calibration Method. An external reference to a citation, such as a DOI, is optional.

class.title: Data_Set
class.description: The Data_Set class is the container for classes and attributes describing the size and version of data sets used by the machine learning model.

class.title: Machine_Learning
class.description: The Machine_Learning class is a container for all machine learning information in the label.

class.title: Machine_Learning_Algorithm
class.description: The Machine_Learning_Algorithm class is a container for classes and and attributes describing the algorithm type and learning style used. An external reference to a citation for the algorithm is required.

class.title: Optimization_Algorithm
class.description: The Optimization_Algorithm class is a container for classes and and attributes describing the optimization algorithm used.

class.title: Preprocessing_Method
class.description: The Preprocessing_Method class contains information about a data set's preprocessing method.

class.title: Test_Performance
class.description: The Test_Performance class contains information about a trained model's performance on the test set.

class.title: Test_Set
class.description: The Test_Set class belongs to the Data_Set class family and contains attributes describing the size and version of the data set used to test the machine learning model (i.e., in terms of generalization to previously unseen data).

class.title: Trained_Machine_Learning_Model
class.description: The Trained_Machine_Learning_Model class is a container for information about how a given model was trained and evaluated. Machine_Learning_Algorithm, Training_Set, Optimization_Algorithm, Trained_Model_Hyperparameter, and Trained_Model_File are required, while Validation_Set, Test_Set, Test_Performance, Trained_Model_Architecture, and Calibration_Method are optional.

class.title: Trained_Model_Architecture
class.description: The Trained_Model_Architecture class is a container for classes and and attributes describing the trained model architecture. An internal reference to the architecture is optional.

class.title: Trained_Model_File
class.description: The Trained_Model_File class is a container for classes and and attributes describing the trained model file. An external reference for the trained model file is required.

class.title: Trained_Model_Hyperparameter
class.description: The Trained_Model_Hyperparameter class is a container for classes and and attributes describing the trained model hyperparameter.

class.title: Training_Set
class.description: The Training_Set class belongs to the Data_Set class family and contains attributes that describe the size and version of the data set used to train the machine learning model.

class.title: Validation_Set
class.description: The Validation_Set class belongs to the Data_Set class family and contains attributes that describe the size and version of the data set used to validate the machine learning model (e.g., to choose the best hyperparameters).

attribute.title: augmentation_method_description
attribute.description: The augmentation_method_description attribute describes the augmentation method in more detail.

attribute.title: augmentation_method_name
attribute.description: The augmentation_method_name attribute names any method by which an image was augmented, e.g. 180 degrees counterclockwise rotation; horizontal flipping; brightness adjustment.

attribute.title: augmentation_method_parameter
attribute.description: The augmentation_method_parameter attribute names any parameters, e.g. gamma.

attribute.title: augmentation_method_parameter_value
attribute.description: The augmentation_method_parameter_value attribute specifies the value of the named parameter, e.g. for a parameter "gamma," the value could be [0.5, 1.5].

attribute.title: calibration_method_description
attribute.description: The calibration_method_description attribute specifies any additional details about the calibration method used.

attribute.title: calibration_method_name
attribute.description: The calibration_method_name attribute specifies the name of the calibration used, e.g. "temperature scaling."

attribute.title: calibration_method_parameter
attribute.description: The calibration_method_parameter attribute specifies the name of the parameter used, e.g. "temperature."

attribute.title: calibration_method_parameter_value
attribute.description: The calibration_method_parameter_value attribute sepcifies the value of the named parameter, e.g. for a parameter "temperature," the value could be "1.31."

attribute.title: data_set_count
attribute.description: The data_set_count attribute provides the number of items in the data set.

attribute.title: data_set_version_id
attribute.description: The data_set_version_id attribute specifies the data set version number.

attribute.title: algorithm_learning_style
attribute.description: The algorithm_learning_style attribute describes the type of learning style employed by the algorithm to solve a problem. Specifically, the learning style depends on whether labeled or unlabeled data was employed to train the model. Labeled data includes observations that are associated with a desired output such as a class or numeric value.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: Both labeled data and unlabeled data were used to inform the model.
Supervised_Learning indicates that labeled data has been used to train a model to yield the desired output.
The algorithm did not employ any labeled data and instead discovered patterns from unlabeled data.

attribute.title: algorithm_name
attribute.description: The algorithm_name attribute specifies the name of the algorithm used.

attribute.title: algorithm_type
attribute.description: The algorithm_type attribute describes the kind of algorithm used, such as a regression model, neural network, tree, etc.

PermissibleValue.valueMeaning: The algorithm used for data analysis is a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) Classifier.

attribute.title: trained_model_objective_function_description
attribute.description: The trained_model_objective_function_description attribute describes the objective function used.

attribute.title: trained_model_objective_function_name
attribute.description: The trained_model_objective_function_name attribute specifies the name of the objective function used.

attribute.title: optimization_algorithm_description
attribute.description: The optimization_algorithm_description attribute specifies any additional details about the optimization algorithm.

attribute.title: optimization_algorithm_name
attribute.description: The optimization_algorithm_name attribute specifies the name of the operation algorithm, e.g. "stochastic gradient descent."

attribute.title: optimization_algorithm_parameter
attribute.description: The optimization_algorithm_parameter attribute specifies the name of a parameter used, e.g. "conv1 learning rate," or "weight decay."

attribute.title: optimization_algorithm_parameter_value
attribute.description: The optimization_algorithm_parameter_value attribute specifies the value of the named parameter, e.g. for a parameter "conv1 learning rate," the value could be "0.001."

attribute.title: preprocessing_method_description
attribute.description: The preprocessing_method_description attribute describes the preprocessing method in more detail.

attribute.title: preprocessing_method_name
attribute.description: The preprocessing_method_name attribute names any method by which an image was preprocessed, e.g. center cropping.

attribute.title: preprocessing_method_parameter
attribute.description: The preprocessing_method_parameter attribute names any preprocessing parameters.

attribute.title: preprocessing_method_parameter_value
attribute.description: The preprocessing_method_parameter_value attribute specifies the value of the named preprocessing parameter.

attribute.title: performance_measure
attribute.description: The performance_measure attribute specifies the name of the measure (or metric) used to report performance of the model on the test set.

attribute.title: performance_score
attribute.description: The performance_score attribute reports the numeric score the model achieved using performance_measure on the test set. Values are not constrained since the measure may not be a strict metric. Examples could include accuracy, loss, runtime, memory consumption, etc.

attribute.title: trained_model_creation_date
attribute.description: The trained_model_creation_date attribute specifies the date that the model was created, in Year/Month/Day format.

attribute.title: trained_model_name
attribute.description: The trained_model_name attribute specifies the name of the model used.

attribute.title: trained_model_version_id
attribute.description: The trained_model_version_id attribute specifies the trained model version number.

attribute.title: trained_model_architecture_description
attribute.description: The trained_model_architecture_description attribute specifies any additional details about the architecture.

attribute.title: trained_model_architecture_name
attribute.description: The trained_model_architecture_name attribute specifies the name of the architecture, e.g. "MSLNet."

attribute.title: trained_model_architecture_version_id
attribute.description: The trained_model_architecture_version_id attribute specifies the architecture version number.

attribute.title: trained_model_file_description
attribute.description: The trained_model_file_description attribute specifies any additional details about the trained model file, e.g. the file format.

attribute.title: trained_model_file_name
attribute.description: The trained_model_file_name attribute specifies the name of the trained model file.

attribute.title: trained_model_hyperparameter_name
attribute.description: The trained_model_hyperparameter_name attribute specifies the name of the hyperparameter, e.g. "batch size," "normalization method," "number of epochs," "conv1 dropout rate," "conv2 dropout rate."

attribute.title: trained_model_hyperparameter_value
attribute.description: The trained_model_hyperparameter_value attribute specifies the value of the hyperparameter named, e.g."z-score" for normalization method, "100" for "number of epochs."
